The Inventory Committee to conduct physical inventory on all PPE owned by the LGU and submit the Report thereon to the Office of the Auditor pursuant to Section 124 of the NGAS Manual for LGUs, Volume I;

The Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer to perform periodic reconciliation of property cards to ensure that all discrepancies are immediately investigated, cleared and reconciled with the books of accounts;

Prepare necessary journal entries to adjust the duly investigated reconciling items in order to reflect the correct account balances;

Maintain complete and accurate Property, Plant and Equipment Ledger Cards (PPELC) for each class of equipment.

Ensure that an approved ordinance from the Sanggunian covers all impositions and collections of fees in the Municipality from the Sangunian;

Fast-track the preparation of a memorandum of agreement between the LGU Cortes and the recipient Peoples' Organization of Madreliňo; and

Properly account all collections by issuing official receipts indicating the actual amount received.

